{
  "texts": [
    "While the above products are aimed at enhancing research workflows, other GAI workflow products are designed for teaching and learning contexts.",
    "An example is Kortext Premium (https://www.kortext.com/premium-live/), an enhanced version of the Kortext study platform.",
    "This multipurpose workspace provides students access to digital textbooks and file storage, as well as generating study notes, summaries, translations, and citations.",
    "Another student learningoriented product is Clarivate's Alethea (https://clarivate.com/products/books/alethea/), a reading assistant that asks students questions and creates tasks for them to facilitate engagement with their reading.",
    "Alethea thus advertises itself as using GAI to make students think more critically, rather than producing work for them."
  ]
}